wdi2-SH.DYN.MORT.def: Under-five mortality rate is the probability per 1,000 that a newborn baby will die before reaching age five, if subject to age-specific mortality rates of the specified year.
wdi2-SH.DYN.MORT.name: Mortality rate
wdi2-SH.DYN.MORT.source: Estimates developed by the UN Inter-agency Group for Child Mortality Estimation (UNICEF, WHO, World Bank, UN DESA Population Division) at www.childmortality.org.
